column5:
@hannahengland - i get where you are coming from, i am just hoping for a glimmer of hope at the end of this long tunnel...
@shaun c - harmony on documentation is the 'holy grail', but as we have seen from the outset, every airline is trying to push the envelope and get the edge over each other, whether that's offering free pcr tests, free insurance etc, i can see why they are doing it, but that's not a long term solution imho. it needs to be government led.
there was talk today (in wales) of allowing travel in a few weeks time (cases/r rate dependant).
even though i was supposed to be travelling on business at the end of march, while i think this is technically still allowed, my company have now posponed this to the 25th may. fingers crossed i can travel with a bit less restriction as i was hoping to take the wife and daughter for a business/holiday combo...
